SPORTS = [
    {"hero":True,"sub":"Tennis","h3":"Wimbledon draw puts Sinner and Djokovic on semi-final path","summary":"The 2026 Wimbledon draw landed seven-time champion Novak Djokovic in defending champion Jannik Sinner's half, while Roland Garros winner Alexander Zverev anchors the bottom section.","body":["The Wimbledon draw was released on Friday June 26 with the grass major running from June 29 to July 12. Djokovic could meet world number one Sinner in the semi-finals, while top seeds Sinner and Zverev head the men's field. Carlos Alcaraz will not take part.","Taylor Fritz opens against home favourite Jack Draper in a blockbuster first round, with Fritz holding a 10-5 head-to-head edge over Zverev that includes seven straight wins. Felix Auger-Aliassime, Ben Shelton, Alex de Minaur and Daniil Medvedev round out the top eight seeds."],"sources":[("ATP Tour","https://www.atptour.com/en/news/wimbledon-2026-draw"),("Perfect Tennis","https://www.perfect-tennis.com/wimbledon-draw-2026/")]},
    {"sub":"Tennis","h3":"Osaka reaches first career grass-court final at Bad Homburg","summary":"Naomi Osaka beat Wang Xinyu to reach her maiden grass final, where she faces Karolina Muchova on Saturday in the last WTA 500 tune-up before Wimbledon.","body":["Osaka enjoyed another routine win in Bad Homburg to set up a Saturday final against Muchova, who advanced with a 6-4, 6-4 victory over qualifier Elena-Gabriela Ruse. It is the first grass-court final of Osaka's career and her best run on the surface to date.","The Bad Homburg Open powered by Solarwatt is the last WTA 500 event before Wimbledon. Earlier in the week Osaka outclassed Elise Mertens to reach her first quarterfinal of the 2026 season."],"sources":[("WTA","https://www.wtatennis.com/news/4527265/osaka-reaches-new-heights-on-grass-by-making-bad-homburg-final"),("Just Women's Sports","https://justwomenssports.com/reads/naomi-osaka-bad-homburg-open-final-2026/")]},
    {"sub":"Tennis","h3":"Eastbourne and Bad Homburg cap off the grass tune-up week","summary":"Jasmine Paolini led the Eastbourne draw alongside Madison Keys and Jelena Ostapenko, while Venus Williams and Alexandra Eala paired up for a doubles run in Bad Homburg.","body":["The Lexus Eastbourne Open, a WTA 250 at Devonshire Park, ran June 22 to 27 with 32 singles players competing in one of the final grass tests before Wimbledon. Paolini entered as the top seed, joined by Grand Slam champions Keys and Ostapenko.","In Bad Homburg, the 45-year-old Venus Williams partnered Alexandra Eala to reach the doubles quarterfinals, beating Catherine Harrison and Alexandra Osborne in straight sets."],"sources":[("WTA Eastbourne","https://www.wtatennis.com/tournaments/710/eastbourne/2026"),("WTA","https://www.wtatennis.com/videos/4526229/venus-williams-eala-set-sail-into-bad-homburg-quarterfinals")]},
    {"sub":"Sailing","h3":"Los Gallos claim first SailGP win of 2026 in Canada","summary":"Diego Botin's Los Gallos secured their maiden event victory of the season at the Canada Sail Grand Prix in Halifax, denying debutants Artemis a first-ever podium top spot.","body":["Los Gallos won Sunday's final at the June 20-21 Canada Sail Grand Prix, becoming one of four different event winners this season. The result denied the Artemis SailGP Team their first win in their debut campaign.","The victory lifted Los Gallos into second in the championship standings on 44 points, level with Emirates Great Britain. The BONDS Flying Roos still lead with 62 points. The next event is the Emirates Great Britain Sail Grand Prix on July 25-26."],"sources":[("SailGP","https://sailgp.com/betting/tips/canada-sail-grand-prix-recap-los-gallos-sailgp-teams-storms-to-halifax-win"),("U.S. SailGP Team","https://www.ussailgpteam.com/standings")]},
    {"sub":"Formula 1","h3":"Antonelli sets the pace in Austrian GP practice at Spielberg","summary":"Championship leader Kimi Antonelli topped both Friday practice sessions at the Red Bull Ring ahead of Sunday's Austrian Grand Prix, edging Oscar Piastri and Lando Norris in FP2.","body":["Antonelli led FP1 with a 1:07.796 and then headed FP2 from Piastri and Norris during the second hour of running in Spielberg. The Austrian Grand Prix is scheduled for Sunday June 28 at the Red Bull Ring.","The Mercedes driver goes into the weekend leading the drivers' championship with 156 points, 41 clear of Lewis Hamilton and 50 ahead of teammate George Russell. Mercedes top the constructors' standings on 262 points."],"sources":[("Formula 1","https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/fp2-antonelli-sets-the-pace-from-piastri-and-norris-during-second-practice-in-austria.SXfZLlntvyYCzyvkPTNPv"),("Motorsport Week","https://www.motorsportweek.com/2026/06/26/formula-1-2026-austrian-grand-prix-fp1-results/")]},
    {"sub":"Formula 1","h3":"Antonelli leads title race as F1 heads into Austria weekend","summary":"The young Mercedes driver carries a commanding points lead into his home-region race, with Hamilton and Russell chasing in a tight constructors' fight.","body":["Antonelli's 156 points give him a 41-point cushion over Hamilton heading into the Austrian round, a remarkable position for the Italian in a Mercedes squad that leads both championships. Russell sits third on 106 points.","Spielberg has historically delivered close racing and the constructors' battle remains live, keeping pressure on the chasing teams as the season approaches its midpoint."],"sources":[("Wikipedia","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_Austrian_Grand_Prix"),("The Race","https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/f1-austrian-gp-2026-practice-results/")]},
    {"sub":"Football","h3":"World Cup knockout stage looms as group play concludes","summary":"The expanded 48-team World Cup wraps its group stage this weekend, with the round of 32 beginning June 28 and the top two from every group plus the best eight third-placed sides advancing.","body":["The tournament across Canada, Mexico and the United States kicked off on June 11 and concludes with the final at MetLife Stadium on July 19. The knockout phase opens June 28 in a single-elimination format.","Brazil topped their group after beating Scotland and will face Japan in the round of 32, while South Africa reached the knockouts for the first time and drew Canada. Switzerland clinched their group ahead of runners-up Canada."],"sources":[("Wikipedia","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_FIFA_World_Cup_knockout_stage"),("ESPN","https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48939282/2026-fifa-world-cup-fixtures-results-match-schedule-group-stage-knockout-rounds-bracket")]},
    {"sub":"Football","h3":"Norway stun France as World Cup group drama peaks","summary":"Norway hammered France 4-1 and Senegal routed Iraq 5-0 on a wild final matchday, while the Netherlands beat Tunisia 3-1 to settle Group F places.","body":["The third round of group games delivered some of the tournament's biggest shocks, headlined by Norway's 4-1 win over France and Senegal's 5-0 demolition of Iraq. The Netherlands closed out Group F with a 3-1 result against Tunisia.","Saturday June 27 brings the last group fixtures, including Argentina against Jordan, England against Panama and Portugal against Colombia, before the knockout bracket locks in."],"sources":[("Yahoo Sports","https://sports.yahoo.com/soccer/article/2026-world-cup-results-standings-and-schedule-live-scores-group-stage-updates-and-how-to-watch-050724193.html"),("FOX Sports","https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/fifa-world-cup/scores")]},
    {"sub":"Football","h3":"Feyenoord land Vanhoutte as Eredivisie summer market heats up","summary":"Feyenoord completed a permanent deal for Belgian midfielder Charles Vanhoutte from Nice, while Premier League clubs circle Dutch talent including AZ's Kees Smit and Ajax's Sean Steur.","body":["Vanhoutte joined Feyenoord on a permanent transfer after a single season at Nice, one of several confirmed Eredivisie moves for the 2026/27 campaign. Activity has picked up sharply across the league this summer.","Paris Saint-Germain are among clubs monitoring AZ Alkmaar's 20-year-old Dutch midfielder Kees Smit, and Liverpool are tracking Ajax midfielder Sean Steur as European sides chase emerging Dutch prospects."],"sources":[("Football Oranje","https://www.football-oranje.com/"),("Transfermarkt","https://www.transfermarkt.us/eredivisie/transfers/wettbewerb/NL1")]},
    {"sub":"Grappling & Judo","h3":"Diego Pato makes history at IBJJF Worlds with record fifth title","summary":"Diego Oliveira, known as Pato, became the winningest light featherweight in jiu-jitsu history at the 30th IBJJF World Championship, surpassing a record held by his own coach.","body":["At the 30th edition of the IBJJF World Championship in Long Beach, Pato took the 64kg black belt title and broke the all-time light featherweight record, passing the four-title mark set by Guilherme Mendes and Robson Moura. He was widely named the event's standout performer.","Other adult black belt champions included Tainan Dalpra at 82kg, Erich Munis in the open class and Mayssa Bastos at 48kg, with AOJ and Checkmat athletes dominating the podiums."],"sources":[("BJJ Heroes","https://www.bjjheroes.com/bjj-news/ibjjf-world-championship-2026-results"),("FloGrappling","https://www.flograppling.com/articles/15951418-ibjjf-worlds-2026-results-heres-every-division-champion")]},
    {"sub":"Grappling & Judo","h3":"ADCC World Championship 2026 set for Krakow in September","summary":"Grappling's premier no-gi event will be staged at Tauron Arena Krakow on September 12-13, with five male divisions of 16 athletes and three female divisions of eight.","body":["The 2026 ADCC World Championship will take place in Poland this September, the sport's biggest stage for submission grappling. The format keeps five male weight classes with 16 competitors each plus three female divisions of eight.","Invitations and qualifying continue to shape the brackets, with FloGrappling tracking the confirmed athlete list ahead of the showpiece event."],"sources":[("FloGrappling","https://www.flograppling.com/articles/15999094-when-is-the-2026-no-gi-bjj-adcc-world-championship"),("ADCC","https://www.adcc2026.com/")]},
    {"sub":"Grappling & Judo","h3":"IJF judo circuit rolls on with late-June World Tour stops","summary":"The international judo calendar continued with World Tour events in China and South America in late June, building toward the 2026 World Championships in Baku this October.","body":["Judo's June schedule featured competitions in Qingdao, China on June 26-28 and Santiago de Chile on June 26-27 as the IJF World Tour and ranking season pressed ahead.","The marquee 2026 World Judo Championships are set for Baku, Azerbaijan from October 4 to 11, with the summer events feeding directly into the world ranking race."],"sources":[("IJF","https://www.ijf.org/calendar?age=world_tour"),("Wikipedia","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_World_Judo_Championships")]},
]

