    {"hero":True,"sub":"Devices & Launches","h3":"Meta drops Ray-Ban name for new $299 Meta Glasses line","summary":"Meta unveiled a trio of self-branded AI glasses starting at $299, ending years of Ray-Ban and Oakley labels as Mark Zuckerberg keeps pushing wearables.","body":["Announced on June 23, the lineup includes the Fury and Adventurer at $299 plus a Kylie Jenner edition at $399, all still built with EssilorLuxottica. The move signals Meta's ambition to own the smart glasses category outright.","New software brings the Muse Spark AI update for better answers, dynamic photos that pick the best shot from a burst, and pedestrian navigation carried over from the Display glasses. Live translation expanded to 20 languages including Mandarin, Korean, Japanese and Arabic."],"sources":[("CNBC","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/06/23/meta-glasses-are-new-smart-glasses-starting-at-299.html"),("Engadget","https://www.engadget.com/2199519/meta-ai-glasses-hands-on-kylie-jenner-edition/")]},
    {"sub":"Devices & Launches","h3":"Samsung Unpacked targets July 22 with Z Fold 8 trio","summary":"Leaks point to a London Unpacked on July 22 where Samsung is expected to reveal the Galaxy Z Fold 8, a wider Fold 8 Ultra and the Z Flip 8 alongside new Galaxy Watch models.","body":["Color and storage details for all three foldables leaked through GSMArena, with the Fold 8 offered in Cream, Graphite, Lavender and Pistachio and the Flip 8 in Cream, Graphite, Mint and Pink. Both Fold models are tipped to run the Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5.","The Flip 8 is expected to gain a crease-free display and a new hinge, with an Exynos 2600 chip in some markets. Samsung is also expected to show the Galaxy Watch Ultra 2 and Watch 9 at the event."],"sources":[("GSMArena","https://www.gsmarena.com/samsung_galaxy_fold8_fold8_ultra_and_flip8_colors_and_storage_options_leak-news-73408.php"),("PhoneArena","https://www.phonearena.com/news/galaxy-unpacked-date-leaks_id180315")]},
    {"sub":"Devices & Launches","h3":"Nintendo teases Splatoon Raiders with Switch 2 Joy-Cons","summary":"Nintendo announced Splatoon Raiders, a new third-person shooter for Switch 2, plus matching pastel Joy-Cons, with a dedicated Direct set for June 30.","body":["The special edition Joy-Cons feature pastel blue and yellow stripes and launch alongside the game on July 23. Nintendo will reveal more at a Raiders Direct on June 30.","The news comes after Nintendo raised Switch 2 pricing earlier in 2026, citing the AI chip memory shortage, with the console set to start at $499.99 in the US from September 1."],"sources":[("Screen Rant","https://screenrant.com/nintendo-new-hardware-june-2026-announced/"),("Wikipedia","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nintendo_Switch_2")]},
    {"sub":"Devices & Launches","h3":"Motorola, Xiaomi and OnePlus crowd the June phone calendar","summary":"A busy June launch window included the Motorola Edge 70 Pro+ with a 50x AI zoom camera and the global OnePlus 15s, as mid-range and flagship rivals jostled for attention.","body":["Motorola confirmed the Edge 70 Pro+ with a 6.8-inch AMOLED panel, MediaTek Dimensity 8500 Extreme chip and a 50MP periscope lens offering 3.5x optical zoom. Xiaomi and Redmi also pushed new models into the market.","The OnePlus 15s is expected globally this month with a 6.32-inch 165Hz AMOLED display, peak brightness of 3,600 nits and the Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5 processor."],"sources":[("Gizmochina","https://www.gizmochina.com/2026/05/29/top-5-upcoming-smartphone-launches-in-june-2026/"),("Techlusive","https://www.techlusive.in/mobile-phones/upcoming-smartphone-launches-in-june-2026-motorola-xiaomi-samsung-and-more-1664376/")]},
    {"sub":"Software & Services","h3":"Google ships June Pixel Drop with Bubbles and Screen Reactions","summary":"The June 2026 Pixel Feature Drop landed with stable Android 17, adding floating app Bubbles, Screen Reactions for selfie overlays and expanded Gemini tools.","body":["Bubbles let apps float over whatever is on screen and shrink into movable icons for faster multitasking, while Screen Reactions overlay a green-screen selfie video on full screen recordings. Gemini gained Lyria 3 music creation and an updated Omni video feature.","The drop arrived with the Android 17 June security update carrying 38 Pixel fixes, and the Pixel Watch added Emergency Sharing tied to Car Crash, Fall and Loss of Pulse detection."],"sources":[("9to5Google","https://9to5google.com/2026/06/16/june-2026-pixel-feature-drop/"),("9to5Google","https://9to5google.com/2026/06/16/android-17-june-update-pixel/")]},
    {"sub":"Software & Services","h3":"Android 17 QPR1 Beta 5 rolls out days after the last beta","summary":"Google pushed Android 17 QPR1 Beta 5 to Pixel devices less than two weeks after Beta 4, continuing rapid bug-fix iteration on the next quarterly release.","body":["The beta arrived on June 23 with fixes for Pixel devices as Google refines the QPR1 cycle. It follows Beta 4 and a 4.1 patch earlier in the month.","Google also detailed new system-level features in its June update, including Parental Controls PIN content restrictions, contact card info in Quick Share and an Ask Play conversational search button."],"sources":[("9to5Google","https://9to5google.com/2026/06/23/android-17-qpr1-beta-5-pixel/"),("9to5Google","https://9to5google.com/2026/06/22/june-2026-google-system-updates/")]},
    {"sub":"Software & Services","h3":"Instagram preps custom fonts and dubbed reels for late June","summary":"Instagram added a WhatsApp profile banner and dubbed reels in broadcast channels, with new custom fonts for Reels and Stories rolling out from June 30.","body":["The platform is testing custom fonts for Notes and bringing fresh typeface options to Reels and Stories starting at the end of the month. A new WhatsApp profile banner links the two Meta apps more tightly.","The updates continue Meta's push to weave its services together and give creators more styling tools across short-form video formats."],"sources":[("SocialBee","https://socialbee.com/blog/instagram-updates/"),("Metricool","https://metricool.com/instagram-news/")]},
    {"sub":"Software & Services","h3":"OpenAI simplifies ChatGPT modes and retires GPT-5.2","summary":"OpenAI replaced a tangle of thinking variants with six plain-language options and moved existing GPT-5.2 chats onto the newer GPT-5.5 models.","body":["From June 10, ChatGPT's reasoning modes became Instant, Medium, High, Extra High, Pro Standard and Pro Extended, aiming to cut confusion over which setting to pick. GPT-5.2 was withdrawn on June 12 with conversations continuing on GPT-5.5.","Users also gained the ability to delete entries on the memory summary page and switch memory off entirely from a single menu, tightening control over stored context."],"sources":[("OpenAI Help Center","https://help.openai.com/en/articles/6825453-chatgpt-on-whatsapp-update"),("Releasebot","https://releasebot.io/updates/openai/chatgpt")]},
    {"sub":"EVs & Mobility","h3":"Tesla expands Austin robotaxi zone but fleet stays tiny","summary":"Tesla said its unsupervised robotaxi service now covers the entire Austin metro, yet the active fleet remains at roughly 20 vehicles serving the expanded area.","body":["The June 3 expansion stretched the service map across all of metro Austin, but coverage data and vehicle counts show the rollout is still modest. Reports peg the unsupervised fleet at fewer than 50 cars in Texas overall.","Tesla has tied any aggressive scaling to its FSD software rewrite, pushing a meaningful ramp toward late 2026 or early 2027 even as the geographic footprint grows."],"sources":[("Electrek","https://electrek.co/2026/06/03/tesla-robotaxi-expands-entire-austin-metro-only-20-vehicles/"),("InsideEVs","https://insideevs.com/news/797263/tesla-robotaxi-texas-fleet/")]},
    {"sub":"EVs & Mobility","h3":"Rivian and GM push vehicle-to-grid charging forward","summary":"Rivian partnered with ChargeScape for managed and bidirectional charging while GM unlocked full vehicle-to-grid capability on existing home systems via a firmware update.","body":["Rivian's June 16 ChargeScape tie-up lets R1S, R1T and R2 owners auto-charge during off-peak hours for potential savings of thousands of dollars a year. The brand's charging network now exceeds 1,000 DC fast ports across 148 sites.","GM shipped a firmware update giving current GM Energy vehicle-to-home setups full vehicle-to-grid function with no new hardware, and announced V2G partnerships with DTE Energy and plans with Pacific Gas & Electric."],"sources":[("InsideEVs","https://insideevs.com/news/798838/rivian-partnership-cheaper-home-charging/"),("Utility Dive","https://www.utilitydive.com/news/managed-bidirectional-ev-charging-advances-with-utility-automaker-support/823171/")]},
    {"sub":"EVs & Mobility","h3":"BYD readies first Europe-only EV with Dolphin G debut","summary":"BYD will unveil the Dolphin G, a B-segment model designed specifically for European buyers, in Berlin in June before a UK showing at Goodwood in July.","body":["Executive vice-president Stella Li said the Dolphin G is the first product BYD has designed for Europe, noting there is no interest in the model in China. Its global debut takes place in Berlin this month.","The compact hatch leads a wider wave of European-specific BYD launches as the Chinese carmaker tailors its lineup to local tastes and regulations."],"sources":[("Autocar","https://www.autocar.co.uk/car-news/new-cars/byd-launch-new-wave-european-specific-models"),("Auto Express","https://www.autoexpress.co.uk/byd/368822/byds-new-car-blitz-just-getting-started-dolphin-g-sealion-8-shark-6-due-soon")]},
    {"sub":"Devices & Launches","h3":"SK Hynix moves to raise $29 billion as AI memory demand surges","summary":"SK Hynix announced plans on June 24 to raise up to $29.4 billion through a secondary listing to expand chip production and meet booming AI memory demand.","body":["The proceeds are earmarked for new fabrication facilities in South Korea and the US as memory makers race to supply AI infrastructure. The move came alongside record results from Micron driven by the same demand.","The capital raise underscores how tight high-bandwidth memory supply has become, with the squeeze rippling into consumer hardware pricing including Nintendo's Switch 2 increase."],"sources":[("Tech Startups","https://techstartups.com/2026/06/25/top-tech-news-today-june-25-2026/"),("LLM Stats","https://llm-stats.com/llm-updates")]},
    {"sub":"Devices & Launches","h3":"Qualcomm eyes Tenstorrent in multibillion-dollar AI chip play","summary":"Qualcomm is reportedly in early talks to acquire RISC-V AI chip designer Tenstorrent for between $8 billion and $10 billion to strengthen its AI hardware position.","body":["Tenstorrent designs AI chips around the open RISC-V standard, and a deal would give Qualcomm a stronger seat at a hardware table currently dominated by Nvidia and AMD. Qualcomm also struck a nearly $4 billion deal to bolster its AI software layer.","The reported talks reflect a broader scramble among chipmakers to assemble full AI stacks spanning silicon and software as demand keeps climbing."],"sources":[("Tech Startups","https://techstartups.com/2026/06/25/top-tech-news-today-june-25-2026/"),("TechCrunch","https://techcrunch.com/category/artificial-intelligence/")]},
    {"sub":"Software & Services","h3":"iOS 26.6 betas seed as encrypted RCS spreads cross-platform","summary":"Apple pushed fresh iOS 26.6 betas to developers as the Liquid Glass era continues, building on encrypted RCS messaging between iPhone and Android.","body":["Apple seeded new iOS 26.6 betas alongside iPadOS, macOS, watchOS and visionOS builds as it refines the iOS 26 cycle. The current public release carries the Liquid Glass redesign, the biggest visual overhaul since iOS 7.","Earlier iOS 26.5 introduced end-to-end encryption for RCS messages exchanged between iPhone and Android, closing a long-standing security gap in cross-platform texting."],"sources":[("MacRumors","https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ios-26/")]},
